3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"OKX calculates FTM/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using the premium index between perpetual and spot prices. The funding rate is capped at ±0.75% per cycle to prevent extreme payments during high volatility. OKX's portfolio margin mode allows cross-collateral positions, enabling more capital-efficient funding rate strategies across multiple Fantom ecosystem tokens."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","FTM","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FTM/USDT funding rates often diverge significantly during Fantom ecosystem events like Andre Cronje announcements or DeFi protocol launches on the network. The pair's mid-tier volume creates opportunities for meaningful rate discrepancies without the intense competition seen in major pairs like BTC or ETH."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FTM/USDT funding rates on OKX have historically ranged from -0.5% to +0.4% during normal market conditions, with extreme spikes during Fantom ecosystem catalysts. The pair exhibits strong correlation with broader DeFi sentiment, often showing negative funding during general altcoin bearishness. Seasonal patterns emerge around Fantom conference announcements and major protocol deployments, typically driving positive funding as leveraged longs increase. Weekend funding tends to be more volatile due to reduced arbitrageur activity and lower spot market liquidity."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Execution"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Profitable FTM/USDT funding arbitrage occurs when rates exceed 0.1% per 8-hour cycle, accounting for OKX's trading fees and potential slippage. The strategy involves shorting perpetuals while buying spot FTM, requiring careful position sizing due to Fantom's price volatility. OKX's API supports automated funding collection, crucial for maintaining delta-neutral positions during rapid FTM price movements. Cross-exchange arbitrage with Binance or Bybit often presents additional opportunities when OKX funding diverges from market consensus."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FTM funding rate arbitrage carries specific risks including Fantom network congestion affecting spot market access and potential depegging during extreme volatility. Position sizing should account for FTM's tendency toward 20-30% daily moves during news events, requiring adequate collateral buffers. OKX's portfolio margin mode helps mitigate liquidation risk but requires monitoring cross-asset exposure limits. Auto-deleveraging risk increases during Fantom ecosystem black swan events when many leveraged positions move in the same direction simultaneously."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What makes FTM funding rates on OKX different from other exchanges?","answer":"OKX's FTM/USDT funding uses a premium index methodology with tighter caps (±0.75%) compared to some competitors. The exchange's strong institutional presence often results in more stable funding during normal conditions but can create arbitrage opportunities during retail-driven Fantom rallies."},{"question":"How does Fantom network activity impact funding rates?","answer":"High Fantom DeFi activity often correlates with positive funding rates as traders leverage long positions to capture ecosystem growth. Network upgrades or Andre Cronje announcements typically spike funding above 0.2% as speculation increases leveraged long interest."},{"question":"What's the minimum position size for profitable FTM funding arbitrage on OKX?","answer":"Given OKX's fee structure and typical FTM funding volatility, positions should exceed $5,000 notional to generate meaningful returns after fees. Smaller positions may still be profitable during extreme funding periods above 0.3% per cycle."},{"question":"How does OKX's portfolio margin affect FTM funding strategies?","answer":"Portfolio margin allows using other crypto holdings as collateral for FTM positions, reducing capital requirements for delta-neutral strategies. However, correlation risk increases during broad crypto selloffs when all collateral assets may decline simultaneously with FTM positions."}]}]
